<font color="#FF0000">WORDS FROM A FREIND</font><br>
<tt>Thu Aug  7 21:17:15 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
A close personal friend sent me the following to share with everyone. Although he has yet to post here, he is with us all in spirit.<br><br>
&quot;Art,<br><br>
In the Wisdom of a great leader from 1500 years past I paraphrase the following and insert some of my own.<br><br>
When we ask a true Warrior to compromise his beliefs, we are asking the Warrior to surrender integrity.  Once such compromises begin they become easier to suggest and harder to refuse.<br><br>
The deepest scars a Warrior bears are not of the body, but of the soul. Wounds to the body heal faster and more thoroughly than those inflicted on the soul and are less threatening to the Warrior, his tribe, or his Nation.<br><br>
Some Warriors are born and others are shaped by their nation, all will never surrender their integrity and no man is powerful enough to take it away.  We were asked to be Warriors and we wear our Honor as Armor.<br><br>
There are those of questionable character who will betray all they profess to Honor.  These men will never know the power of a Warriors soul or the freedom of his spirit.  A oneness only we can understand.&quot;<br><br>

<p><code>--   (Arthur Varanelli) </code><p>


